tldr: The agent evaluated the codebase against the SOW for a sleep questionnaire
  application, identified missing database, dashboard, and authentication
  features, and then implemented a plan to add these, including a PostgreSQL
  database for responses, a simple password-protected admin dashboard with CSV
  export, and updated demographics.
overview: The user initiated a project to implement database storage, an admin
  dashboard, and authentication for a "Sleep Questionnaire Application" based on
  a provided SOW. The agent first assessed the existing codebase, identifying
  that questionnaire response storage, CSV export, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system were missing. After clarifying the desired
  authentication complexity (simple password) and demographic fields (combining
  SOW and existing fields), the agent proceeded with the implementation. This
  involved updating demographic types and form fields, creating a Prisma model
  for  in , and developing API
  routes for saving, retrieving, and exporting responses as CSV. A simple
  cookie-based authentication system was built, along with a login page and an
  admin dashboard to display responses with pagination and CSV download
  functionality. Finally, the questionnaire form was modified to submit data to
  the new database endpoint.
